<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="219" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="18.[136,1451,1490,1661]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
So far known from 
<collectingCountry box="[415,483,1526,1552]" name="Brazil" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<typeStatus box="[500,553,1526,1552]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">type</typeStatus>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[574,697,1526,1552]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lucking, A." box="[714,876,1526,1553]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" refId="ref23662" refString="Lucking, A. (1995) Diversitat und Mikrohabitatpraferenzen epiphyller Moose in einem tropischen Regenwald in Costa Rica. Dissertation zur Erlangung des Doktorgrades Dr. rer. nat. Der Fakultat fur Naturwissenschaften der Universitat Ulm. 211 p." type="book" year="1995">Lücking 1995</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName box="[921,1129,1526,1552]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Leptolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="convexistipa">
<emphasis box="[921,943,1527,1552]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">L.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[989,1129,1527,1552]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">convexistipa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and 
<collectingCountry box="[1203,1296,1526,1552]" name="Ecuador" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(Heinrichs et al. 2014); however, its distribution is incompletely known since it was included in the polymorphous 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mitt.) Schiffn." authorityName="Schiffn." baseAuthorityName="Mitt." class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Leptolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[1315,1451,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">L. maculata</emphasis>
(Mitt.) Schiffn.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Grolle, R." box="[318,457,1598,1625]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" pagination="191 - 216" refId="ref22235" refString="Grolle, R. (1976) Drepanolejeunea subgen. Kolpolejeunea - eine neue Untergattung aus der Palaotropis. Journal of the Hattori Botanical Laboratory 40: 191 - 216." type="journal article" year="1976">Grolle 1976</bibRefCitation>
). Recent molecular studies provided some evidence that this complex may include several species, and therefore 
<taxonomicName box="[386,556,1635,1660]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Leptolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="convexistipa">
<emphasis box="[386,556,1635,1660]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">L. convexistipa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was kept separately (
<bibRefCitation author="Heinrichs, J. &amp; Schafer-Verwimp, A. &amp; Czumay, A. &amp; Dong, S. &amp; Scheben, A. &amp; Feldberg, K. &amp; Schneider, H." box="[798,1049,1634,1661]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" pagination="165 - 174" refId="ref23317" refString="Heinrichs, J., Schafer-Verwimp, A., Czumay, A. Dong, S., Scheben, A., Feldberg, K. &amp; Schneider, H. (2014 a) Towards a monophyletic classification of Lejeuneaceae I: subtribe Leptolejeuneinae subtr. nov. Phytotaxa 156: 165 - 174. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 156.3.7" type="journal article" year="2014">Heinrichs et al. 2014a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
